        h1.border-blue-lighter.border-b-4.mb-4.px-20.w-full About Florida Keys National Marine Sanctuary

        p(class="w-5/6 italic") Did you know that Florida Keys National Marine Sanctuary protects North America’s only living coral barrier reef? From beautiful reefs and lush kelp forests to deep-sea canyons and mysterious underwater shipwrecks, national marine sanctuaries located around the country protect some of our nation’s most unique riches.
        
        p(class="w-5/6 pt-2 italic") In this section, you will learn about the National Marine Sanctuary System, the history of Florida Keys National Marine Sanctuary, and about the areas and resources that the sanctuary protect.

